This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it proposes a new DNN model that replaces multiplications with shifts and adds, which can reduce energy consumption while maintaining accuracy. Additionally, the paper uses the MNIST and CIFAR-10 datasets to experimentally verify the performance of the proposed model, which is a common practice in the cs.NE category. 

The paper is also likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category as it discusses the accuracy and energy consumption of DNNs in the context of image classification tasks. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) category is also a likely fit as the paper proposes a new DNN model that aims to balance accuracy and energy consumption, which is a common goal in machine learning research. 

The paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category as it discusses the energy consumption of DNNs, which is an important consideration in robotics applications. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category as it proposes a new DNN model that can reduce energy consumption, which is an important consideration in control systems design.
